FAQs
1. What are the language requirements for studying in Lithuania?
Most universities in Lithuania offer programs in English, especially at the postgraduate level. Proficiency in English is typically required, and you may need to submit TOEFL or IELTS scores. Some programs are taught in Lithuanian, in which case proficiency in Lithuanian is necessary.

2. Are there scholarships available for international students in Lithuania?
Yes, many Lithuanian universities and government programs offer scholarships to international students based on academic merit, financial need, or other criteria. These scholarships can help cover tuition fees and living expenses.

3. How much does it cost to live in Lithuania as a student?
The cost of living in Lithuania is generally affordable. Monthly expenses, including accommodation, food, transportation, and entertainment, can vary but are relatively low compared to many Western countries. On average, students might spend between $400 to $700 per month.



